A '''birthgasm''' is a [[female orgasm]] that occurs during [[childbirth]]. This is sometimes referred to as an "orgasmic childbirth."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.unassistedchildbirth.com/orgasmic-childbirth/|title=Orgasmic Childbirth — Unassisted Childbirth|publisher=Unassistedchildbirth.com|date=|accessdate=2015-11-28}}</ref> Some women use sexual stimulation to ease [[Uterine contraction#Childbirth|contractions]], instead of [[anesthesia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.foxnews.com/story/2009/01/05/foxsexpert-orgasms-during-childbirth-it-happens.html|title=FOXSexpert: Orgasms During Childbirth? It Happens|publisher=Fox News|date=2009-01-05|accessdate=2015-11-28}}</ref> More than 85% of midwives surveyed by Postel (2013) stated that a sexually pleasurable birth experience was possible, and 69% stated they had observed such a case.<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Mayberry|first1=Lorel|last2=Daniel|first2=Jacqueline|title='Birthgasm': A Literary Review of Orgasm as an Alternative Mode of Pain Relief in Childbirth|journal=Journal of Holistic Nursing|date=16 November 2015|pmid=26578553|doi=10.1177/0898010115614205|volume=34|issue=4|pages=331–342}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last1=Postel|first1=T.|title=Childbirth Climax: The Revealing of Obstetrical Orgasm|journal=Sexologies|date=October 2013|volume=22|issue=4|pages=e89–e92|doi=10.1016/j.sexol.2013.03.011}}</ref>

