{{Infobox book| | name = | image = | image_caption = | author = [[René Barjavel]] | title_orig = | translator = Eileen Finletter | country = [[France]] | language = [[French language|French]], [[English language|English]] | publisher = [[Presses de la Cité]] | pub_date = 1973 | english_pub_date = 1974 | pages = 344 }} '''''The Immortals''''' ({{Lang-fr|'''Le Grand secret'''}}) is a 1973 novel by the French writer [[René Barjavel]]. It tells the story of a grand conspiracy between world leaders in order to hide the existence of a contagious virus which makes humans immortal. It was published in [[English language|English]] in 1974, translated by Eileen Finletter.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.worldcat.org/title/immortals/oclc/868103|title=The immortals.|work=[[WorldCat]]|accessdate=2015-05-08}}</ref>
The book received the [[Prix Maison de la Presse]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.prixmaisondelapresse.org/laureats-du-prix-maison-de-la-presse|title=Lauréats du prix Maison de la presse|language=French|work=prixmaisondelapresse.org|publisher=Syndicat national des dépositaires de presse|accessdate=2015-05-08|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141011140129/http://www.prixmaisondelapresse.org/laureats-du-prix-maison-de-la-presse|archivedate=2014-10-11|df=}}</ref> It was adapted into the 1989 television serial ''[[Le grand secret]]'', directed by Jacques Trébouta.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.notrecinema.com/communaute/v1_detail_film.php3?lefilm=12060|title=Le grand secret (TV)|language=French|work=Notre Cinéma|accessdate=2015-05-08}}</ref>
